SIMPLE: mannered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mannered
<hw>Man"nered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a
certain way, esp. a polite way, of carrying and conducting one's self;
<as>as, a well-<ex>mannered</ex> child</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Give her princely training, that she may be⟦br⟧
<qex>Mannered</qex> as she is born.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affected with mannerism; marked by excess of some
characteristic peculiarity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His style is in some degree <qex>mannered</qex> and confined.</q>
<rj><qau>Hazlitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mannerism</ent>⟦br⟧
